<paragraph id="2A174E6C9A3D30985E3B91C67C2DCF3A" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">NHMUK 1914.4.3.41, lectotype (ex Preston).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="21FBF3647142EC9D70BCDBC773B7B229" pageId="41" pageNumber="58" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="6E2437C011203E40058B75E55A7B92A9" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1F13173B28A6DA4CCF464724B8285059" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">
This varietal name has been treated as unavailable under Art. 45.6 ICZN by 
<bibRefCitation id="8CC70D2FBC93DADC8B17CCBA07A4565E" author="Breure, ASH" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="46" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 367" publicationUrl="10.3897/zookeys.392.6328" refId="B14" refString="Breure, ASH, Ablett, JD, 2014. Annotated type catalogue of the Bulimulidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda, Orthalicoidea) in the Natural History Museum, London. ZooKeys 392: 1 - 367, DOI: 10.3897/zookeys.392.6328" title="Annotated type catalogue of the Bulimulidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda, Orthalicoidea) in the Natural History Museum, London." url="10.3897/zookeys.392.6328" volume="392" year="2014">Breure and Ablett (2014</bibRefCitation>
: 96). Paul Callomon (pers. commun.) has suggested that this should be reconsidered and doubted if a lectotype of the nominal name already existed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267BE1BF812A88F2A33A6A635CC2F60E" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="F6BD520C87AB2B387B2CCF3F262B3D0C" bold="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">Our opinion is as follows:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A88012D7AC3C5A1AD54AF98B480D628" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">
Preston undoubtedly had a series of specimens at hand when describing 
<taxonomicName id="4E5E4F0B432C9728EA34F73A723239E4" authorityName="Preston" authorityYear="1909" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Bulimulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bulimulus (Drymaeus) interruptus" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="interruptus" subGenus="Drymaeus">Bulimulus (Drymaeus) interruptus</taxonomicName>
; both the wording &quot;to be greatly variable&quot; and &quot;its principle forms&quot; are indicative of this.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B934E4124C8E90F48757473E318D5CB6" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">
<bibRefCitation id="5A6E2D63D79457526ADFA480CBDE6D25" author="Breure, ASH" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden" pageId="45" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 215" refId="B10" refString="Breure, ASH, 1979. Systematics, phylogeny and zoogeography of Bulimulinae (Mollusca). Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden 168: 1 - 215" title="Systematics, phylogeny and zoogeography of Bulimulinae (Mollusca)." volume="168" year="1979">Breure (1979</bibRefCitation>
: 120) mentioned this taxon in his listing under 
<taxonomicName id="CC818D61420ED819D73ED4895FA84067" authority="" authorityName="Albers" authorityYear="1850" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Drymaeus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Drymaeus (Mesembrinus)" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Mesembrinus">Drymaeus (Mesembrinus)</taxonomicName>
Albers, 1850, and stated &quot;HT BMNH 1914.4.3.38&quot; [referring to a single specimen, thus qualifying Art. 74.6.1.2 jo. 74.3]; Art. 74.6 ICZN rules this statement as a lectotype designation. It should be noted, however, that Breure did not list the &quot;var. 
<taxonomicName id="2B5E887531EEB8EC0178845E3B064E1A" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Drymaeus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="var. pallidus" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="interruptus" variety="pallidus">
<emphasis id="029079082734686F8D183AA0F94573CC" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">pallidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; of Preston in his paper (cf. point d below).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EE75C588BF4C1F7E4FBBF2704B3CBD25" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">
<normalizedToken id="3F5E42BD285AB8536C75853547981C58" originalValue="Köhler">Koehler</normalizedToken>
(1997) also concluded that this taxon was described from several specimens but said &quot;A holotype has not been designated. Therefore, the present specimen [ZMB 59597] is a syntype. Consequently, the specimen in the BMNH referred to as holotype by 
<bibRefCitation id="6CCFC90A5727A5C2FABBF980A1A7155D" author="Breure, ASH" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden" pageId="45" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 215" refId="B10" refString="Breure, ASH, 1979. Systematics, phylogeny and zoogeography of Bulimulinae (Mollusca). Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden 168: 1 - 215" title="Systematics, phylogeny and zoogeography of Bulimulinae (Mollusca)." volume="168" year="1979">Breure (1979)</bibRefCitation>
is a syntype&quot;. Overlooking, as explained in the previous item, the lectotype designation under Art. 74.6 (see previous point).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AD97199B8DA8EA1EBA6E61AB03D45CD5" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">
Reconsidering the (un)availability under Art. 45.6, it is important to note that var. 
<taxonomicName id="B0A13B9844B9C9C99373A80CAA99EECB" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Drymaeus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="var. pallidus" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="interruptus" variety="pallidus">
<emphasis id="98CEEF0E0511845D5653EBB1CEEFA699" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">pallidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was proposed before 1961 and has to be treated as subspecific (see the contributions of Steve Lingafelter and Doug Yanega on the Taxacom listing, http://to.ly/zFZO). It may be noted that the only reference to this taxon after 
<normalizedToken id="14822A17EC2F73FFABCF9121AC36CAD5" originalValue="Preston’s">Preston's</normalizedToken>
publication is in 
<bibRefCitation id="A8F14DAD9A5798ADC564CBA09203A473" author="Baker, HB" journalOrPublisher="Occasional Papers of the Museum of Zoology, University of Michigan" pageId="45" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 49" refId="B5" refString="Baker, HB, 1926. The Mollusca collected by the University of Michigan-Williamson expedition in Venezuela, IV. Occasional Papers of the Museum of Zoology, University of Michigan 167: 1 - 49" title="The Mollusca collected by the University of Michigan-Williamson expedition in Venezuela, IV." volume="167" year="1926">Baker (1926</bibRefCitation>
: 44), who regarded it as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="28F1B3A87B17346755C338D93B19E6C3" authority="Scopoli, 1777" authorityName="L.Pfeiffer" authorityYear="1848" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Bulimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bulimus granadensis" order="Pulmonata" pageId="41" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="granadensis">
<emphasis id="0D4F95F6A722AAA6BA889ECAF2FE308D" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">Bulimus granadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pfeiffer, 1848 (see also 
<bibRefCitation id="1C7DC753B4E93D317ABB132CF94FD342" author="Richardson, CL" journalOrPublisher="Tryonia" pageId="51" pageNumber="68" refId="B114" refString="Richardson, CL, 1995. Bulimulidae: catalog of species. Tryonia 28" title="Bulimulidae: catalog of species." volume="28" year="1995">Richardson 1995</bibRefCitation>
: 133).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5CFB9A0341FB508AD249CBC802DB9309" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">
While 
<taxonomicName id="AC044E6B3F3C3AE7211EC1906964B0FA" authorityName="Preston" authorityYear="1909" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Bulimulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bulimulus (Drymaeus) interruptus subsp. var. var. pallidus" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="interruptus" subGenus="Drymaeus" subSpecies="var." variety="pallidus">Bulimulus (Drymaeus) interruptus var. pallidus</taxonomicName>
is an available name, we concur with 
<bibRefCitation id="9F324ED2FF8AE0BECF568C0E93DAC3B7" author="Baker, HB" journalOrPublisher="Occasional Papers of the Museum of Zoology, University of Michigan" pageId="45" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 49" refId="B5" refString="Baker, HB, 1926. The Mollusca collected by the University of Michigan-Williamson expedition in Venezuela, IV. Occasional Papers of the Museum of Zoology, University of Michigan 167: 1 - 49" title="The Mollusca collected by the University of Michigan-Williamson expedition in Venezuela, IV." volume="167" year="1926">Baker (1926)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="C9F5CC990DD8BE88FA658C68E0272C30" author="Richardson, CL" journalOrPublisher="Tryonia" pageId="51" pageNumber="68" refId="B114" refString="Richardson, CL, 1995. Bulimulidae: catalog of species. Tryonia 28" title="Bulimulidae: catalog of species." volume="28" year="1995">Richardson (1995)</bibRefCitation>
to consider this taxon as a synonym of the nominal form.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="614DB1BABA08FFB2100FE73869B7238A" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">
The specimen of var. 
<taxonomicName id="32CB96185508394F15FFA90067CF5B1B" authorityName="Preston" authorityYear="1909" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Bulimulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="var. pallidus" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="41" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="interruptus" variety="pallidus">
<emphasis id="D905892EA154A090677076DB140E8B19" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">pallidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the NHMUK is now designated lectotype (
<emphasis id="A0578CD3B8ACAD6959B1B5131D079CFF" bold="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">design. n.</emphasis>
) to fixate this synonymisation. The text in 
<bibRefCitation id="A4593CA0482480E555D370CC12BCB1CD" author="Breure, ASH" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="46" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 367" publicationUrl="10.3897/zookeys.392.6328" refId="B14" refString="Breure, ASH, Ablett, JD, 2014. Annotated type catalogue of the Bulimulidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda, Orthalicoidea) in the Natural History Museum, London. ZooKeys 392: 1 - 367, DOI: 10.3897/zookeys.392.6328" title="Annotated type catalogue of the Bulimulidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda, Orthalicoidea) in the Natural History Museum, London." url="10.3897/zookeys.392.6328" volume="392" year="2014">Breure and Ablett (2014</bibRefCitation>
: 96), under 'Type 
<normalizedToken id="39A0DC49166D22F729E0F6819585B081" originalValue="material’">material'</normalizedToken>
, should be corrected as follows: &quot;NHMUK 1914.3.38, lectotype; 1914.4.3.39-40, 42-43, four paralectotypes&quot;.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D01A192E6B0A4473D64DE46EF54114FE" pageId="41" pageNumber="58" type="current systematic position">
<paragraph id="9773B61B0FC98CBCD60FE19F696DC9B2" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">Current systematic position.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="12512C7161D7E5D8EB74B3193C017B07" pageId="41" pageNumber="58">
